SIMPLE: farinaceous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Farinaceous
<hw>Far`i*na"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>farinaceus</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Consisting or made of
meal or flour; <as>as, a <ex>farinaceous</ex> diet</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Yielding farina or flour; <as>as,
<ex>ffarinaceous</ex> seeds</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Like meal; mealy; pertaining to meal; <as>as, a
<ex>farinaceous</ex> taste, smell, or appearance</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Farinose</ent>⟦br⟧
